<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'><div>=== {{incharacter|Where can I get leather patches, rags and other components?}} ===</div></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'><div>=== {{incharacter|Where can I get leather patches, rags and other components?}} ===</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'>−</td><td class='diff-deletedline'><div>* '''[[Rag]]s''': Cut any item made of cotton (like a pair of [[jeans]] or a [[sheet]]). To cut it you need to {{k|a}}ctivate a knife-like tool in your inventory ([[pocket knife]], [[steak knife]], [[combat knife]], etc - check the [<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">[tools</del>]<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">] page </del>for any item with a &quot;<del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">knife</del>&quot; <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">function</del>), select {{k|1}} to cut-up fabric and then choose the item in your inventory you want to cut. For [[t-shirt]]s and [[tank top]]s you can [[Crafting#Disassembling_items|disassemble]] them instead (via {{k|(}}).</div></td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div>* '''[[Rag]]s''': Cut any item made of cotton (like a pair of [[jeans]] or a [[sheet]]). To cut it you need to {{k|a}}ctivate a knife-like tool in your inventory ([[pocket knife]], [[steak knife]], [[combat knife]], etc - check the [<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">http://cdda-trunk.chezzo.com/qualities/CUT item browser</ins>] for any item with a &quot;<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">cutting</ins>&quot; <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">quality</ins>), select {{k|1}} to cut-up fabric and then choose the item in your inventory you want to cut. For [[t-shirt]]s and [[tank top]]s you can [[Crafting#Disassembling_items|disassemble]] them instead (via {{k|(}})<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">. Using the {{k|b}}utcher menu you can also cut up or dissassemble item on the ground, if you have the correct tools</ins>.</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'>−</td><td class='diff-deletedline'><div>* '''[[Leather patch]]es''': You have the easy way and the hard way. The easy way is to cut leather items following the process mentioned above (items like [[purse]]s, [[sneakers]], [[leather jacket]]s, [[leather pants]] and [[leather gloves]], etc. Check the [[clothing]] page for a complete list). The hard way is by {{k|B}}utchering, and tanning the resulting skin, from creatures with a thick skin (like [[giant frog]]s), or apply a knife to a fur pelt.  </div></td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div>* '''[[Leather patch]]es''': You have the easy way and the hard way. The easy way is to cut leather items following the process mentioned above (items like [[purse]]s, [[sneakers]], [[leather jacket]]s, [[leather pants]] and [[leather gloves]], etc. Check the [[clothing]] page for a complete list). The hard way is by {{k|B}}utchering, and tanning the resulting skin, from creatures with a thick skin (like [[giant frog]]s), or apply a knife to a fur pelt.</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td></tr>
