<tr><td class='diff-marker'>−</td><td class='diff-deletedline'><div>You might be in pain from getting attacked, reducing your speed. Back off while you can if you don't want to be crippled by pain.</div></td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div>You might be in pain from getting attacked, reducing your speed. Back off while you can if you don't want to be crippled by pain<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">. Check your {{k|@}} character screen for any speed penalties. Check your armor encumbrance too. Having high encumbrance on your arms can slow down your attacks</ins>.</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'><div>=== {{incharacter|I can't hit anything with my gun! What's happening here?!}} ===</div></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'><div>=== {{incharacter|I can't hit anything with my gun! What's happening here?!}} ===</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'>−</td><td class='diff-deletedline'><div>You're either not [[skills|skilled]] enough yet in the skill used to fire your gun, <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">or </del>you aren't taking the [[recoil]] effect into account. <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Low dexterity</del>, or <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">using </del>a <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">gun </del>with <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">high sight dispersion and  dispersion values</del>. <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Use </del>{{k|.}} to aim <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">longer</del>, <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">this increases </del>the <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">confidence </del>value.</div></td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div>You're either not [[skills|skilled]] enough yet in the skill used to fire your gun, you aren't taking the [[recoil]] effect into account<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">, or you aren't properly aiming</ins>. <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Remember that pressing {{k|a}}, {{k|c}}</ins>, or <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">{{k|p}} (standard '''</ins>a<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">'''iming, '''c'''areful aiming, and '''p'''recise aiming respectively) while targeting </ins>with <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">a ranged weapon can drastically increase your chances of hitting by having your character take longer to do so</ins>. <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">Using </ins>{{k|.}} <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">to wait allows you to finely control how long you want </ins>to aim, <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">letting you to decide </ins>the <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">exact timing of your shot. Other things that could be impacting your ability to shoot include a low dexterity, using a gun with high sight dispersion/dispersion </ins>value<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">, or encumbrance on your arms</ins>.</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'><div>=== {{incharacter|I have this whip/spear, how do I use it at longer ranges?!}} ===</div></td><td class='diff-marker'> </td><td class='diff-context'><div>=== {{incharacter|I have this whip/spear, how do I use it at longer ranges?!}} ===</div></td></tr>
<tr><td class='diff-marker'>−</td><td class='diff-deletedline'><div>Wield it, and {{k|f}}ire it. Same for other ranged weapons.</div></td><td class='diff-marker'>+</td><td class='diff-addedline'><div>Wield it, and {{k|f}}ire it<ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">. Use your movement keys to move the cursor onto what you wanna Slash/shoot</ins>. Same for other ranged weapons.</div></td></tr>
